## Stack

Flutter app with **GetX**, **Dio**, and **clean-style layering** (`presentation` / `data` / `infrastructure`). Production quality: disposal, loading/error paths, centralized session/API behavior.

## Cursor layout (official)

- **Rules (this folder):** short, persistent policies — see [Rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules).
- **Skills:** `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` — on-demand playbooks — see [Skills](https://cursor.com/docs/skills).
- **Subagents:** `.cursor/agents/*.md` — specialized delegation — see [Subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents).

## Before coding

1. Match patterns in `lib/`.
2. Open relevant **skills** only when the task needs depth (Agent discovers them; or invoke with `/skill-name` in chat).
3. For **Hey Team** mode, see root `AGENTS.md` and `agents/AGENTS.md`.

## Do not

Break architecture, scatter 401 handling, or use quick hacks that skip error/session rules.
